properties.otherAdvice:

  • Motorists going towards International Airport or Marsh St should keep to the right of the median construction site, south of Robey St.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Summer Holiday Period - SHOALHAVEN Naval College Rd, Booderee Ave, Cyrus St at Northern Hyams Beach
properties.otherAdvice:
Changed traffic conditions and speed reductions will be in place approaching Hyams Beach including one-way roads at the northern end of Hyams Beach to manage the heavy traffic over the busy period until 27 January.    

  • A temporary roundabout will be in operation on Cnr Naval College Rd and Booderee Ave from 7am to 6pm daily. 
  • Speed reduction from 80km/h to 40km/h will be in effect along Naval College Rd approaching Booderee Ave in both directions.   
  • One way traffic changes will be in place on Tulip St (northbound only), Cyrus St (southbound only), Bamboo Ave (westbound only) and Anemone Ave (eastbound only).    

If Hyams Beach reaches capacity, or in the event of a catastrophic fire danger rating, temporary closures at  Naval College Rd and Booderee Ave will be implemented.   

Motorists should arrive early or expect significant delays on roads approaching the township and beach during this period.  Alternative white sand beaches can be found at Website: Shoalhaven – South Coast NSW.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Summer Holiday Period

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS traffic changes and long term road closures - BADGERYS CREEK Elizabeth Dr/Badgerys Creek Rd near Lawson Road
properties.otherAdvice:
As part of the Western Sydney Airport Project, there is traffic changes and long term road closures to complete the ultimate design of Elizabeth Dr and Badgerys Creek Rd.

From 4am Mon 20 Jan the following traffic changes will be in operation:

Traffic will switch to a newly constructed Badgerys Creek Rd. This new Badgerys Creek link Rd will join Elizabeth Dr.
• Existing Badgerys Creek Rd will be closed permanently between Elizabeth Dr and Pitt St.

Elizabeth Dr traffic will switch over to the newly constructed carriageway.
• A new roundabout at the intersection of Elizabeth Dr and the new link of Badgerys Creek Rd which has been shifted and realigned.
• Barriers are placed eastbound along Elizabeth Dr and the roundabout to complete pavement works on the existing Elizabeth Dr.

Tracks and trails are open, excluding the Mining Road fire trail and the Mungo walking track.
